            <title>[THRIFT-5404] Connection timeout errors from TSocket are not treated as timeouts</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5404</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In TSocket.Open, when connect timeout happens, we &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/e27e82c46ba4d46c2c3267701191cdc26614f739/lib/go/thrift/socket.go#L169&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;wrap it into TTransportException with type NOT_OPEN&lt;/a&gt;, but in&#160;TTransportException.Timeout &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/e27e82c46ba4d46c2c3267701191cdc26614f739/lib/go/thrift/transport_exception.go#L75&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;we only treat TIMED_OUT as time outs&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
